Make sure you got perl and libwww-perl installed

If you want to install kfilefactory just for you then follow these steps:

1) run ./install.sh , verify the commands it prints and execute them

2) Right click on a file or directory -> Actions -> Share file

If you want to install kfilefactory for all the users then follow the steps below as super user.

1) open kfilefactory.desktop using any editor and change last line to Exec=/usr/libexec/kde4/kfilefactory "%F"

2) run ./install_root.sh

3) Right click on a file or directory -> Actions -> Share file